Box Produce Management System - Java
This Java program simulates a box produce management system, allowing users to manage the contents of a produce box and make selections based on certain conditions.

Overview
The Box Produce Management System is designed to perform the following tasks:

Initialize a box with produce items.
Randomly select produce items for the box.
Allow users to enter their preferred produce items.
Process produce selections based on specific conditions.

Features
Random produce selection: The system randomly selects produce items to populate the box.
User input: Users can enter their preferred produce items.
Salsa offer: A salsa recipe flier is provided based on produce choices.

How to Run
Clone or download the repository to your local machine.
Open the project in your Java development environment.
Compile and run the main class to start the program.

Usage
The program initializes a produce box with a set of available produce items from the contents.txt file.
Produce items are randomly selected for the box.
Users are prompted to enter their preferences for three produce items.
The program processes the selections, applying special conditions for salsa offer.
The updated contents of the box are displayed along with salsa offers.

Files
boxProduce.java: Defines the boxProduce class responsible for managing produce items and selections.
main.java: Contains the main class with the program's logic.
contents.txt: Contains the list of available produce items.

Dependencies
None

Contributions
Contributions are welcome! If you'd like to enhance the program or add new features, feel free to fork this repository, make your changes, and submit a pull request.
